{{Infobox artist | bgcolour = | name = Andrés Waissman | image = Andres Waissman.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Andrés Waissman at his studio, 2010 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date |1955|7|14}} | birth_place = [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] | nationality = {{flag|Argentina}} | ocupation = [[Artist]] | period = (1973-present) | field = [[Painting]], [[drawing]] | website = www.andreswaissman.net }}
'''Andrés Waissman''' is a visual artist born in [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]], in 1955. A relevant figure of Argentinian and Latin-American contemporary art, he is known for paintings such as ''Multitudes'', ''Black & White'', and his most recent work, ''Virutas''. He lives and works in Buenos Aires.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://elgranotro.com.ar/index.php/waissman-un-artista-emblematico-en-el-universo-simbolico-del-arte-contemporaneo/ |access-date=Jun 15, 2015 |publisher=El Gran Otro |language=spanish |title=Waissman, un artista emblemático en el universo simbólico del arte contemporáneo }}</ref>
==Life==
Waissman was born in Buenos Aires on July 14, 1955.<ref>{{citation|title=Al Límite, Arte Global|author =Ignacio Rojas|location=Santiago de Chile|publisher=Publicaciones Arte Al Límite LTDA|year=2013|accessdate=Sep 14, 2015|pages=112}}</ref> The third and last son of Carlos Luis Waissman and Regina Tchira, he had a close relationship with the art world since he was a child. Trained in independent workshops,<ref>{{citation|title=Andrés Waissman, un artista peregrino|author1=Rodrigo Alonso |author2=Jordi Aladro |author3=Fabiana Barreda |author4=Florencia Gró |author5=María Paula Zacharías |location=Buenos Aires|publisher=Proietto & Lamarque|year=2005|accessdate=Sep 1, 2015|pages=211}}</ref> he began exhibiting quite early in the mid 1970s, having his first solo shows at 'Lirolay Gallery' in 1973 and 1977, respectively.<ref>{{citation|title=Galería Lirolay 1960-1981|author =Nelly Perazzo|location=Buenos Aires|publisher=MACLA Editorial|year=2011|accessdate=Sep 20, 2015|pages=215, 218}}</ref> At the same time, he hosted AM and FM radio programs, interviewing critics, intellectuals and artists of various artistic expressions. In 1974 he worked in the studio of Augusto Torres in [[Barcelona]], and in 1978 in [[Paris]] with [[Antonio Seguí]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vos.lavoz.com.ar/artes/andres-waissman-estos-trabajos-van-componiendo-una-vision-global-del-destierro |access-date=Oct 24, 2015 |publisher=Suplemento Vos, La Voz del Interior |language=spanish |title=Andrés Waissman: estos trabajos van componiendo una visión global del destierro }}</ref> In 1984 he moved to [[San Francisco]], where he worked at the Argentinian Consulate as the cultural attaché.<ref>{{citation|title=Andrés Waissman, un artista peregrino|author1=Rodrigo Alonso |author2=Jordi Aladro |author3=Fabiana Barreda |author4=Florencia Gró |author5=María Paula Zacharías |location=Buenos Aires|publisher=Proietto & Lamarque|year=2005|accessdate=Sep 2, 2015|pages=210}}</ref> It was while he was at the consulate that his career developed internationally,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artnet.com/artists/andr%C3%A9s-waissman/biography|access-date=Jul 20, 2015 |publisher=ArtNet |language=english |title=Andrés Waissman, artist biography }}</ref> exhibiting in galleries and museums in [[Los Angeles]], San Francisco, [[New York City|New York]], and cities throughout Europe.<ref>{{citation|title=Andrés Waissman, un artista peregrino|author1=Rodrigo Alonso |author2=Jordi Aladro |author3=Fabiana Barreda |author4=Florencia Gró |author5=María Paula Zacharías |location=Buenos Aires|publisher=Proietto & Lamarque|year=2005|accessdate=Sep 1, 2015|pages=212}}</ref>
In 1992 he returned to Buenos Aires,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artnet.com/artists/andr%C3%A9s-waissman/biography|access-date=Jul 20, 2015 |publisher=ArtNet |language=english |title=Andrés Waissman, artist biography }}</ref> where he began teaching. For three and a half years he and Marina Pellegrini co-hosted ''Styles'', a television program dedicated to rescuing cultural values, especially in the [[visual arts]].<ref>{{citation|title=Andrés Waissman, un artista peregrino|author1=Rodrigo Alonso |author2=Jordi Aladro |author3=Fabiana Barreda |author4=Florencia Gró |author5=María Paula Zacharías |location=Buenos Aires|publisher=Proietto & Lamarque|year=2005|accessdate=Sep 1, 2015|pages=216}}</ref> In 1995 he opened "Dock del Plata Espacio de Arte", the first showroom in [[Puerto Madero]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.registrodeartistas.com.ar/artistas/ver/andres-waissman |access-date=Nov 21, 2015 |publisher=Registro de Artistas|language=spanish |title=Andrés Waissman }}</ref> It became one of the most prestigious studios in the city until its closure in 1998. After the closure of the studio, Andrés Waissman began to work as a curator and communicator, advising many national public officers and agencies in projects and cultural management strategies.<ref>{{citation|title=Andrés Waissman, un artista peregrino|author1=Rodrigo Alonso |author2=Jordi Aladro |author3=Fabiana Barreda |author4=Florencia Gró |author5=María Paula Zacharías |location=Buenos Aires|publisher=Proietto & Lamarque|year=2005|accessdate=Nov 1, 2015|pages=218}}</ref>
In 2005 the book ''Waissman/a pilgrim artist'' was published.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tematika.com/libros/arte__arquitectura_y_diseno--9/artistas_y_movimientos--2/argentinos--2/waissman___bilingue--427800.htm |access-date=Oct 15, 2015 |publisher=Tematika |language=spanish |title=Waissman | first1=Rodrigo | last1=Alonso | first2=Jordi Aladro |last2=Font | first3=Fabiana | last3=Barreda | first4=Florencia | last4=Gro | first5=María Paula | last5=Zacharias}}</ref> In November 2010 the documentary ''[[Waissman]]'', by [[Eduardo Montes Bradley]], premiered on [[WPBT]] Channel 2 (PBS) in the United States, as well as being shown at the [[Museo de Arte Latinoamericano de Buenos Aires]] (MALBA).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arteenlared.com/latinoamerica/argentina/estrenan-en-argentina-el-documental-waissman.html |access-date=Aug 8, 2015 |publisher=Arte en la RED |language=spanish |title=Estrenan en Argentina el documental "Waissman" |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808030529/http://www.arteenlared.com/latinoamerica/argentina/estrenan-en-argentina-el-documental-waissman.html |archive-date=2014-08-08 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
Since 2012 Waissman, along with Rodrigo Alonso, Carlos Herrera, Gabriel Valansi and Eduardo Stupía, has been one of the head teachers for "Proyecto PAC: Prácticas Artísticas Contemporáneas", an annual meeting with a program of art analysis, critique and production.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.proyectopac.com/equipo.html |access-date=Dec 10, 2015 |publisher=Proyecto PAC |language=spanish |title=Equipo Proyecto PAC }}</ref> He continues working on his art and developing new art related projects in his studio in Palermo, Buenos Aires, where he also leads a Studio Cri Program and workshops.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.artnet.com/artists/andr%C3%A9s-waissman/biography|access-date=Oct 10, 2015 |publisher=ArtNet |language=english |title=Andrés Waissman, artist biography }}</ref>
==Exhibitions== He has had several solo exhibitions and more than sixty collective exhibits in both Argentina and international cities.<ref>{{citation|title=Andrés Waissman, un artista peregrino|author1=Rodrigo Alonso |author2=Jordi Aladro |author3=Fabiana Barreda |author4=Florencia Gró |author5=María Paula Zacharías |location=Buenos Aires|publisher=Proietto & Lamarque|year=2005|accessdate=Oct 1, 2015|pages=217}}</ref> His work is part of private collections and museums in [[England]], [[Belgium]], [[Italy]], [[Israel]], the United States, [[Venezuela]], Argentina, and [[Chile]], among others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://townsendcenter.berkeley.edu/events/multitudes|access-date=Jul 20, 2015 |publisher=The Doreen B. Townsend Center for the Humanities |language=english |title=MULTITUDES, Paintings by Andrés Waissman }}</ref> He has also participated in international fairs such as: the Pinta in [[London]]; the Lisbon Art Fair; the Miami International Art Fair; the Chicago Contemporary & Classic Art Fair; Ch.ACO in [[Santiago de Chile]]; the Miart Fiera Internazionale d'Arte Moderna e Contemporanea Milano; and the arteBA in Buenos Aires.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://elgranotro.com.ar/index.php/waissman-un-artista-emblematico-en-el-universo-simbolico-del-arte-contemporaneo/ |access-date=Jun 17, 2015 |publisher=El Gran Otro |language=spanish |title=Waissman, un artista emblemático en el universo simbólico del arte contemporáneo }}</ref>
