In the book, Thurman interprets the teachings of [[Jesus]] through the experience of the oppressed and discusses [[nonviolence|nonviolent]] responses to oppression. The book developed out of a series of lectures that Thurman presented at [[Huston–Tillotson University|Samuel Huston College]] in [[Austin, Texas]] during April 1948."<ref>{{cite book |last=Thurman |first=Howard |date=2012 |title=Jesus and the Disinherited |url= |location=Boston, MA |publisher=Beacon Press |page=8 |isbn=0807010294 |author-link= }}</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=April 2017}}
